burgoo
Homonym Number:  1
Word Class: noun
Sense Number:
Definition:coarse porridge (esp. oatmeal porridge), often in later use, humorously, for `porridge'.
Origin:
Register:
Register 2:
Domain: [none]
Region: [none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: ca1941-1945 R.C. Prison use for `coarse porridge' ca1950s Les Cleveland and N.C.C. Small <i>burgoo</i> for `porridge' common among trampers and mountaineers
